Reasoning: The paper proposes a framework for optimization of an expensive-to-compute function using adaptive random sampling, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the application of the framework on several machine learning problems, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
